.key NAME/A
.bra {
.ket }
; ccon-speed - run the console benchmark with IDENTICAL settings every
; time, so three runs in three consoles are actually comparable.
;
;   Execute S:ccon-speed CCON
;   Execute S:ccon-speed CON
;   Execute S:ccon-speed ViNCEd
;
; Run each one INSIDE the console you are measuring - open a shell on
; that console first, then run this in it. Results append to
; RAM:conbench.txt, all three in the one file.
;
; The point of the script rather than typing the command: REPS and the
; output file must not drift between runs. A benchmark compared against
; a differently-configured benchmark is worse than no benchmark.
;
; Takes a couple of minutes per console. The screen will flood - that
; is the test.
Echo "conbench: measuring {NAME} - this floods the window, give it a minute"
conbench {NAME} TO RAM:conbench.txt REPS 3
